<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Bug on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/bug/</link><description>Recent content in Bug on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/bug/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] ORA-00600: Internal Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-00600/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-00600/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="ora-00600-internal-error"&gt;ORA-00600: Internal Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ORA-00600 is an Oracle internal error that indicates a bug in the Oracle kernel code. It is raised when the database encounters an unexpected internal condition that it cannot handle gracefully.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A known Oracle bug triggered by specific data patterns or operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data corruption in tablespaces or data blocks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insufficient resources (memory, file descriptors) causing internal failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Running an Oracle version with known ORA-00600 defects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-the-trace-file"&gt;Check the Trace File&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Trace files are in the dump directory&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls -lt $ORACLE_BASE/diag/rdbms/&amp;lt;db_name&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;instance&amp;gt;/trace/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Look for files with &amp;#34;ora&amp;#34; in the name&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="search-for-the-first-argument"&gt;Search for the First Argument&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# The error format is: ORA-00600: internal error code, arguments: [arg1], [arg2], ...&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Search Metalink/My Oracle Support for the first argument&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# e.g., ORA-00600: [kcbz_check_objd_typ_3]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="apply-latest-patch-set"&gt;Apply Latest Patch Set&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check current version&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;SELECT * FROM v$version;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Download and apply latest CPU/PSU from Oracle Support&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="check-for-block-corruption"&gt;Check for Block Corruption&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Run RMAN block check
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;BACKUP VALIDATE &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;CHECK&lt;/span&gt; LOGICAL &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DATABASE&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Check specific tablespace
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; v$database_block_corruption;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="try-to-open-database-in-restricted-mode"&gt;Try to Open Database in Restricted Mode&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- If database won&amp;#39;t open
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;STARTUP MOUNT;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;DATABASE&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;OPEN&lt;/span&gt; RESTRICTED;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-sql" data-lang="sql"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Internal error during query
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;SELECT&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;FROM&lt;/span&gt; large_table &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;WHERE&lt;/span&gt; id &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;123&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ORA-00600: internal error code, arguments: [kdsgrp1], [], [], [], [], [], [], []
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Fix: check for block corruption with RMAN
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Error during DDL
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ALTER&lt;/span&gt; TABLESPACE users &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ADD&lt;/span&gt; DATAFILE;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- ORA-00600: internal error code, arguments: [4194], [30], [25], [], []
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;-- Fix: apply latest patch set
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-01555/"&gt;ORA-01555&lt;/a&gt; — snapshot too old&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/oracle/ora-04031/"&gt;ORA-04031&lt;/a&gt; — shared memory allocation failure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>